column2: The Tales of Ba Sing Se
column378: Book 2, Episode 14: A set of vignettes about each of the main characters' adventures in Ba Sing Se, providing a glimpse of their personalities and private lives.
column391: The Tales of Ba Sing Se

column378: Book 1, Episode 5: The group arrives at the Earth Kingdom city of Omashu, where Aang discovers the king is his old friend Bumi, who reveals Aang's destiny: master the other three elements and defeat Fire Lord Ozai.
Book 1, Episode 14: Aang, Katara, and Sokka travel to a village that relies solely on the predictions of a cloud-reading fortuneteller.
Book 2, Episode 9: Aang begins his earthbending training with Toph, but loses confidence in himself when he encounters difficulty with the earth element, the natural opposite of air.
Book 3, Episode 20: Ozai accidentally unlocks Aang's chakra, causing him to enter the Avatar State. The show comes to a dramatic conclusion.

column2: Sozin's Comet, Part 1: The Phoenix King
column378: Book 3, Episode 17: Aang prepares to fight Fire Lord Ozai, but has difficulty deciding how to defeat him without taking his life. In his sleep, Aang is drawn toward a mysterious island that appears suddenly in the sea.
column391: Sozin's Comet, Part 1: The Phoenix King

column378: Book 3, Episode 6: Aang and Zuko each learn about the relationship between Avatar Roku and Fire Lord Sozin; their childhood friendship, falling out, and Sozin's eventual betrayal of Roku to his death.
Book 1, Episode 11: The gang arrives at the Great Divide where Aang helps 2 rival villages cross the canyon together by fabricating a story about their ancestors.
Book 3, Episode 15: The imprisoned members attempt to escape the Boiling Rock against Azula and the group returns to the Western Air Temple.
Book 2, Episode 7: After deciding he would be better off on his own and leaving his uncle, Zuko continues his journey alone and ends up in an Earth Kingdom town.
